msgstr "Si le backend devient injoignable en plein flux."

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.is_available:1 of
msgid "Perform a lightweight health check against the backend."
msgstr "Effectue un contrôle de santé léger du backend."

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.is_available:3 of
msgid "Must never raise; any failure must be caught and returned as False."
msgstr ""
"Ne doit jamais lever ; tout échec doit être attrapé et retourné comme "
"False."

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.is_available:5 of
msgid "True if the backend is reachable and ready, False otherwise."
msgstr "True si le backend est joignable et prêt, False sinon."

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.parse_tool_call:1 of
msgid "Extract narrative text and tool-call JSON from a raw LLM response."
msgstr "Extrait le texte narratif et le JSON de tool call d'une réponse LLM brute."

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.parse_tool_call:3 of
msgid "Resilient parsing:"
msgstr "Parsing résilient :"

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.parse_tool_call:5 of
msgid ""
"Checks for common markdown fences (``~~~json``, triple-backtick json, "
"etc)."
msgstr ""
"Cherche les blocs markdown courants (``~~~json``, triple backtick json, "
"etc)."

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.parse_tool_call:7 of
msgid "Fallback: heuristic search for JSON objects or arrays."
msgstr "Repli : recherche heuristique d'objets ou de tableaux JSON."

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.parse_tool_call:8 of
msgid ""
"Normalizes minor schema deviations (e.g., missing 'stats' key or flat "
"params)."
msgstr ""
"Normalise les écarts de schéma mineurs (ex. clé 'stats' manquante ou "
"paramètres à plat)."

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.parse_tool_call:11 of
msgid "The complete raw string returned by the LLM."
msgstr "La chaîne brute complète retournée par le LLM."

#: axiom.backends.base.LLMBackend.parse_tool_call:13 of
msgid ""
"A (narrative_text, tool_call) tuple — narrative_text is the response with"
" the JSON block removed, and tool_call is the parsed dict/list, or None "
"if no valid JSON was found."
msgstr ""
"Un tuple (narrative_text, tool_call) — narrative_text est la réponse "
"débarrassée du bloc JSON, et tool_call est le dict/la liste parsé, ou "
"None si aucun JSON valide n'a été trouvé."

#: ../../api/backends.md:10
msgid "`axiom.backends.gemini`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.gemini:1 of
msgid "llm_engine/gemini_client.py"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.gemini:3 of
msgid "LLM backend client for Google Gemini models (remote / cloud fallback)."
msgstr "Client backend LLM pour les modèles Google Gemini (distant / repli cloud)."

#: axiom.backends.gemini:5 of
msgid ""
"Uses the google-genai SDK (google.genai).  The client translates Axiom "
"AI's internal list[LLMMessage] format to Gemini's Content objects: the "
"first system-role message becomes the model's system_instruction, and the"
" remaining turns become the contents list."
msgstr ""
"Utilise le SDK google-genai (google.genai).  Le client traduit le format "
"interne list[LLMMessage] d'Axiom AI en objets Content de Gemini : le "
"premier message de rôle system devient le system_instruction du modèle, "
"et les tours restants deviennent la liste contents."

#: axiom.backends.gemini:10 axiom.backends.ollama:9 of
msgid "Typical usage::"
msgstr "Usage typique ::"

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient:1 of
msgid "LLM backend targeting Google Gemini via the google-genai SDK."
msgstr "Backend LLM ciblant Google Gemini via le SDK google-genai."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient:3 of
msgid "Google Generative AI API key."
msgstr "Clé API Google Generative AI."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient:4 of
msgid "Gemini model identifier. Defaults to \"gemini-2.0-flash\"."
msgstr "Identifiant du modèle Gemini. Par défaut \"gemini-2.0-flash\"."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient:6 of
msgid "Soft rate limiter (TICKET-031). 0 = unlimited."
msgstr "Limiteur de débit doux (TICKET-031). 0 = illimité."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient:7 of
msgid ""
"Model tried when the primary model's quota is still exhausted after the "
"retries (quotas are per-model). \"\" = none."
msgstr ""
"Modèle tenté quand le quota du modèle principal reste épuisé après les "
"retries (les quotas sont par modèle). \"\" = aucun."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.is_available:1 of
msgid "Check whether the Gemini API is reachable with the configured key."
msgstr "Vérifie si l'API Gemini est joignable avec la clé configurée."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.is_available:3 of
msgid ""
"Attempts to list available models.  Returns True on success, False on any"
" exception.  Never raises."
msgstr ""
"Tente de lister les modèles disponibles.  Retourne True en cas de succès,"
" False sur toute exception.  Ne lève jamais."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.is_available:6 of
msgid "True if the API responds without error, False otherwise."
msgstr "True si l'API répond sans erreur, False sinon."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.list_models:1 of
msgid "Return the generation-capable model names, without the \"models/\" prefix."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.list_models:3 of
msgid ""
"Empty list on any error — best-effort, used by the settings dialog's "
"model picker (TICKET-062)."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.complete:1 of
msgid "Send messages to Gemini and return a parsed LLMResponse."
msgstr "Envoie les messages à Gemini et retourne une LLMResponse parsée."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.complete:3 of
msgid ""
"Translates list[LLMMessage] into Gemini format: - The first message with "
"role=\"system\" becomes system_instruction. - Remaining messages map "
"user/assistant → user/model roles."
msgstr ""
"Traduit list[LLMMessage] au format Gemini : - Le premier message avec "
"role=\"system\" devient system_instruction. - Les messages restants "
"mappent user/assistant → rôles user/model."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.complete:7
#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.stream_tokens:3
#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.complete:3
