msgid "LLMResponse with narrative_text, optional tool_call, finish_reason."
msgstr "LLMResponse avec narrative_text, tool_call optionnel, finish_reason."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.complete:17 of
msgid "On network failure or API error."
msgstr "Sur échec réseau ou erreur d'API."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.complete:18 of
msgid "On unexpected response structure or bad tool-call JSON."
msgstr "Sur structure de réponse inattendue ou JSON de tool call invalide."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.generate_image_bytes:1 of
msgid "Generate an image from a text prompt and return the raw bytes."
msgstr "Génère une image depuis un prompt texte et retourne les octets bruts."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.generate_image_bytes:3 of
msgid ""
"Used by the \"gemini\" image backend (axiom/image_generator.py) with an "
"image-capable model (e.g. \"gemini-2.5-flash-image\"). Goes through the "
"same quota-resilience path as text calls (TICKET-031 pacing/429 retry, "
"TICKET-033 status/cancellation hooks)."
msgstr ""
"Utilisé par le backend d'images \"gemini\" (axiom/image_generator.py) "
"avec un modèle capable de produire des images (ex. \"gemini-2.5-flash-"
"image\"). Passe par le même chemin de résilience aux quotas que les "
"appels texte (cadencement/retry 429 TICKET-031, hooks de "
"statut/annulation TICKET-033)."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.generate_image_bytes:8 of
msgid "Visual prompt describing the image."
msgstr "Prompt visuel décrivant l'image."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.generate_image_bytes:9 of
msgid ""
"Optional aspect ratio supported by the API (\"1:1\", \"16:9\", ...). "
"Omitted if the installed SDK does not expose ImageConfig."
msgstr ""
"Ratio d'aspect optionnel pris en charge par l'API (\"1:1\", \"16:9\", "
"...). Omis si le SDK installé n'expose pas ImageConfig."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.generate_image_bytes:13 of
msgid ""
"The image bytes (PNG/JPEG as returned by the API), or None if the "
"response contains no image part."
msgstr ""
"Les octets de l'image (PNG/JPEG tels que retournés par l'API), ou None si"
" la réponse ne contient aucune partie image."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.generate_image_bytes:16 of
msgid "On network failure, API error or exhausted quota."
msgstr "Sur échec réseau, erreur d'API ou quota épuisé."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.generate_image_bytes:17 of
msgid "If cancel_event is set during a retry wait."
msgstr "Si cancel_event est armé pendant une attente de retry."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.stream_tokens:1 of
msgid "Yield tokens from a streaming Gemini response."
msgstr "Produit les tokens d'une réponse Gemini en streaming."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.stream_tokens:10
#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.stream_tokens:13 of
msgid "Individual token strings in arrival order."
msgstr "Les tokens individuels dans leur ordre d'arrivée."

#: axiom.backends.gemini.GeminiClient.stream_tokens:12 of
msgid "On network failure."
msgstr "Sur échec réseau."

#: ../../api/backends.md:17
msgid "`axiom.backends.universal`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.universal:1 of
msgid "llm_engine/universal_client.py"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.universal:3 of
msgid ""
"Universal OpenAI-compatible API client for Axiom AI. Supports any "
"local/remote backend that implements the OpenAI /v1/chat/completions API "
"(e.g., LM Studio, KoboldCPP, Ollama, standard OpenAI, etc.)."
msgstr ""
"Client universel d'API compatible OpenAI pour Axiom AI. Prend en charge "
"tout backend local/distant implémentant l'API OpenAI /v1/chat/completions"
" (ex. LM Studio, KoboldCPP, Ollama, OpenAI standard, etc.)."

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient:1 of
msgid "OpenAI-compatible LLM client using httpx."
msgstr "Client LLM compatible OpenAI utilisant httpx."

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient:3 of
msgid "The base URL (e.g., http://localhost:1234/v1)."
msgstr "L'URL de base (ex. http://localhost:1234/v1)."

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient:4 of
msgid "Optional API key for authorization."
msgstr "Clé API optionnelle pour l'autorisation."

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient:5 of
msgid "The model identifier to request."
msgstr "L'identifiant du modèle à demander."

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient:6 of
msgid ""
"Optional headers merged into every request. Lets a provider use a non-"
"Bearer auth scheme (e.g. Anthropic's x-api-key + anthropic-version) — "
"pass api_key=\"\" then."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient:9 of
msgid ""
"Optional cap on the number of stop sequences sent (OpenAI rejects more "
"than 4; most providers have no limit)."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient:11 of
msgid ""
"Optional pool of spare Bearer keys. When a request fails with an "
"auth/quota status (401/402/403/429), the client switches to the next key "
"— stickily — and retries, until the pool is exhausted (TICKET-062: shared"
" beta keys). Only meaningful with Bearer auth (`api_key`)."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient.stream_tokens:1 of
msgid "Yield individual tokens as they arrive via SSE."
msgstr "Produit les tokens individuels à mesure qu'ils arrivent via SSE."

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient.is_available:1 of
msgid "Check if the backend is reachable."
msgstr "Vérifie si le backend est joignable."

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient.list_models:1 of
msgid "Return the model ids exposed by the server's /models endpoint."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.universal.UniversalClient.list_models:3 of
msgid ""
"Empty list on any error — callers use this as a best-effort check (e.g. "
"the settings dialog verifying the configured model exists)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../api/backends.md:24
msgid "`axiom.backends.ollama`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.ollama:1 of
msgid "llm_engine/ollama_client.py"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.backends.ollama:3 of
msgid "LLM backend client for locally running Ollama instances."
msgstr "Client backend LLM pour les instances Ollama locales."

#: axiom.backends.ollama:5 of
msgid ""
"Ollama exposes an OpenAI-compatible REST API.  This client targets the "
"/api/chat endpoint for multi-turn conversation and /api/tags for the "
"health check.  Both streaming and non-streaming modes are supported."
msgstr ""
"Ollama expose une API REST compatible OpenAI.  Ce client cible l'endpoint"
" /api/chat pour la conversation multi-tours et /api/tags pour le contrôle"
" de santé.  Les modes streaming et non-streaming sont pris en charge."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient:1 of
msgid "LLM backend targeting a locally running Ollama server."
msgstr "Backend LLM ciblant un serveur Ollama local."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient:3 of
msgid "Base URL of the Ollama HTTP API. Defaults to \"http://localhost:11434\"."
msgstr "URL de base de l'API HTTP d'Ollama. Par défaut \"http://localhost:11434\"."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient:5 of
msgid "Name of the Ollama model to use (e.g. \"llama3.2\")."
msgstr "Nom du modèle Ollama à utiliser (ex. \"llama3.2\")."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.is_available:1 of
msgid "Check whether the Ollama server is running and reachable."
msgstr "Vérifie si le serveur Ollama tourne et est joignable."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.is_available:3 of
msgid ""
"GETs /api/tags.  Returns True on HTTP 200, False on any exception. Never "
"raises."
msgstr ""
"Fait un GET sur /api/tags.  Retourne True sur HTTP 200, False sur toute "
"exception. Ne lève jamais."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.is_available:6 of
msgid "True if the server responds with HTTP 200, False otherwise."
msgstr "True si le serveur répond HTTP 200, False sinon."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.complete:1 of
msgid "Send messages to Ollama's /api/chat and return a parsed LLMResponse."
msgstr ""
"Envoie les messages au /api/chat d'Ollama et retourne une LLMResponse "
"parsée."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.complete:4 of
msgid "Ignored here; use stream_tokens() for token streaming."
msgstr "Ignoré ici ; utiliser stream_tokens() pour le streaming de tokens."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.complete:7
#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.stream_tokens:9 of
msgid "If \"json\", forces Ollama to return a JSON object."
msgstr "Si \"json\", force Ollama à retourner un objet JSON."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.complete:13 of
msgid "On connection refused, timeout, or HTTP 5xx."
msgstr "Sur connexion refusée, timeout ou HTTP 5xx."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.complete:14 of
msgid "On malformed response JSON or invalid tool-call block."
msgstr "Sur JSON de réponse malformé ou bloc de tool call invalide."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.stream_tokens:1 of
msgid "Yield tokens from Ollama's streaming NDJSON response."
msgstr "Produit les tokens de la réponse NDJSON en streaming d'Ollama."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.stream_tokens:3 of
msgid ""
"POSTs to /api/chat with stream=true and yields each content token as it "
"arrives."
msgstr ""
"POSTe sur /api/chat avec stream=true et produit chaque token de contenu à"
" mesure qu'il arrive."

#: axiom.backends.ollama.OllamaClient.stream_tokens:15 of
msgid "On connection failure or HTTP 5xx."
msgstr "Sur échec de connexion ou HTTP 5xx."

